No. 126,

Misc.

Hoyt v. Florida. Herbert B. Ehrmann and C. J. Hardee, Jr. for appellant. Richard W. Ervin, Attorney General of Florida, and George R. Georgieff, Assistant Attorney General, for appellee.

Appeal from the Supreme Court of Florida. Motion for leave to proceed in forma pauperis granted. Probable jurisdiction noted, and case transferred to appellate docket.
